.container.about-container
  .row
    .col-md-5
      %h1
        About
      %p
        ServiceDesignKIT provides a comprehensive overview of existing design techniques for digital services and supports their selection and application. 
  .row
    .col-md-5
      %p
        Each design technique is represented by flipcards including a short description as well as a step-by-step instruction on how to execute it. It combines a top-down taxonomy-based classification and a bottom-up tag-based classification with an interactive search function allowing easy access to the design techniques. ServiceDesignKIT is an open platform allowing people to contribute with comments and add further design techniques. 
  .row
    .col-md-3
      %p
        ServiceDesignKIT is provided by the research group <a href="http://issd.iism.kit.edu/">"Information Systems & Service Design"</a> (Prof. Dr. Alexander Maedche) of the <a href="http://www.iism.kit.edu/">Institute of Information Systems and Marketing (IISM)</a> and <a href="http://www.ksri.kit.edu/">Karlsruhe Service Research Institute (KSRI)</a> at the <a href="http://www.kit.edu/">Karlsruhe Institute of Technology (KIT)</a>, Germany. 
    .col-md-2
      .logo
        = image_tag("kit_logo.png", :alt => "KIT-Logo", class:"kit_logo")
  .row
    .col-md-5
      %p
      ServiceDesignKIT was developed by Erwin Leung as part of a research project carried out by Xuanhui Liu. The source code can be found on <a href="https://github.com/ServiceDesignKIT/ServiceDesignKIT"></a>, where you also can find further information from a technical perspective.
  .row
