      %p
      %h3
        More information to the taxonomy-based classification
      %p  
        %b Design Phase:
        usually regarded as preconditions when choosing design techniques.
        %br/
        Planning: making a plan for an entire design process.
        %br/
        Draft Prototype: designers make a series of assessments to compare their prototypes with each other to select the appropriate ones.
        %br/
        Detailed Prototype: Design techniques focus on evaluating the design works in detail to modify the prototypes to get a stable version
        %br/
        Launching: Design techniques concentrate on collecting long-term feedback to help designers to improve digital services further and to prepare for the next iteration.
      %p
        %b Evaluation Type:
        indicate how to evaluate an outcome of a design activity.
        %br/
        Observation: designers observe user behavior.
        %br/
        Questionnaire: to measure users’ goal achievement, satisfaction, etc. based on retrospective memory. 
        %br/
        Group Discussion: share ideas in a group to make a decision.
        %br/
        Interview: generate rich data that reveals users’ previous experience and prospect.
        %br/
        Experiment: reflect user behavior in a specific environment by means of concrete data.
      %p
        %b Time Dependency:
        discriminates between immediate emotional feedback and feedback based on memory during interaction with digital services.
        %br/
        Retrospective: Design techniques indicate the dynamics of emotion based on users’ impressions of the experience and the goal achievement.
        %br/
        Real Time: Design techniques are applied to reveal various users’ immediate emotional feedback. 
      %p
        %b User Participation:
        When real users should become involved depends on their roles and design purposes in different design phases.
        %br/
        User Involved: real users are involved in design processes.
        %br/
        Without Real User: real users are not involved in the design activity, but some fictitious user profiles may be used.
      %p
        %b Duration: 
        is based on the specific time length in an iteration cycle of design processes.
        %br/
        Short Term: design activities are conducted in short time period.
        %br/
        Long Term: demonstrate how relationships between digital services and users evolve.
        %br/
        %br/
        %br/
